{Gambits in open games were the popular openings in the nineteenth century.
This preference changed when Lasker became the world champion. Solid
positional play became the style of many new masters. Four gambit tournaments
were organised at the beginning of the twentieth century. The aim was to
revive the popularity of gambits.  The obligated opening of the international
Gambitturnir Wien 1903 was the King's Gambit Accepted. Baron Albert von
Rothschild contributed to the fund of 8000 Crowns. Ten masters played double
rounds in the premisses of the Wiener Schachklub from 2 until 26 v 1903. The
winner became the legendary gambit player Chigorin (13/18) before Marshall
(111/2) and Marco (11). Marco wrote the tournament book.   The success of Wien
1903 led to the organisation of an event for the King's Gambit Defence.
Professor Rice and the Wiener Schachklub made 1500 Crowns available. The event
was played in Vienna from 29 ix 1904 until 14 i 1905. Ten masters played
double rounds. Vidmar had to retire due to illness after six rounds. Maroczy
arrived on 17 xii 1904 and caught up many games. Schlechter (141/2/18) won the
tournament before Maroczy (14). Perlis (10) became third. Gilliam researched
the event.   The masters had to play the King's Gambit Accepted in Abbazia
(Opatija) 1912. Playing hall was the Casino des Etrangers from 14 i until 13
ii. Twelve men played double rounds. The gambit scored negatively in the event.
Rudolf Spielmann, knight of the King's Gambit, achieved an incredible 101/2/11
in the first cycle and won the first prize of 1000 Crowns. Duras became second.
E. Cohn and Reti shared the third place. Marco announced a tournament book but
it never appeared. Gilliam and others reconstructed the event later.  The
Kasino-Klub was established in Baden bei Wien on 23 ii 1914. A gambit event
was announced the next month. Ten masters played double rounds at Kaiser Franz
Ring 7 from 5 iv until 1 v 1914. The participants were allowed to play all
gambits, except for the Queen's Gambit. Only open games were started. Selected
openings by White were the Danish Gambit, King's Gambit, Scotch Gambit and
Evans Gambit. Black was allowed to refuse the gambit. Probably the opening's
choice was steered by beauty prizes for certain gambits. Spielmann (121/2/18),
Tartakower (111/2), Schlechter (11) and Breyer (101/2) won the prizes. 4925
Crowns were payed for prizes and consolation.   Fifty-six games have been
selected from the four tournaments. These encounters are presented by gambit. 
  DANISH GAMBIT  The Danish Gambit is reached by 1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. c3.
Schlechter put forward the counter gambit 3. .. dxc3 4. Bc4 d5! Reti and
Tartakower followed this advise successfully.   } 1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. c3
dxc3 4. Bc4 d5 $6 {He plays a defence advised by Schlechter.} 5. Bxd5 cxb2 6.
Bxb2 Nf6 7. Nf3 ({Right is} 7. Bxf7+ $1) 7... Bb4+ 8. Kf1 O-O $2 ({
More solid is} 8... Qe7 $1) 9. Qb3 $2 {White misses the presented chance.} ({
Great complications are began by} 9. Bxf7+ $1 Kxf7 $5 10. Qb3+ {(Marco)} 10...
Kg6 $1 11. Ne5+ $5 Kh5 12. Qxb4 Qd1+ 13. Qe1 Qxe1+ 14. Kxe1 Nxe4 15. f3 Nd6 16.
h4 $1) 9... Nc6 10. Nc3 ({The pointe is} 10. Bxc6 bxc6 11. Qxb4 Rb8 $1 12. Qd4
Rxb2 $1) 10... Qe7 11. a3 Bd6 12. Re1 Ne5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. Bc4 c6 15. h4 b5
16. Be2 Be6 17. Qc2 Qc5 18. Rc1 Rfd8 19. g3 a5 20. Qb1 Rd2 21. Nd5 Rxb2 22.
Qxb2 Qxd5 23. exd5 Bxb2 24. Rc2 Bxd5 {Reti got two beauty prizes for this game.
} 0-1

