{FALKBEER'S COUNTER-GAMBIT  The gambit 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 is answered by the
counter-gambit 2. .. d5. If White plays the opening correctly, he will gain a
slight advantage, but Black has sufficient compensation for the sacrificed
pawn.  } 1. e4 e5 2. f4 d5 3. exd5 e4 4. d3 {
Black has to proceed as a counter-gambit.} 4... Qxd5 $6 ({
The main line continues by} 4... Nf6 5. dxe4 Nxe4 6. Nf3 Bc5 7. Qe2 Bf5 $1 (
