{ABBAZIA DEFENCE  If Black answers the King Knight's Gambit 1. e4 e5 2. f4
exf4 3. Nf3 by 3. .. d5, he makes the least compromising move. A name for the
opening is the Modern Defence. More usual is the Abbazia Defence, because it
was applied in this gambit tournament frequently.   } 1. e4 e5 2. f4 exf4 3.
Nf3 d5 4. exd5 Nf6 5. Nc3 c6 $6 {A slight provocation is played.} 6. d4 $5 (6.
dxc6 Nxc6 {opens the game as well (Maroczy - Swiderski, Wien 1903).}) 6... Nxd5
7. Nxd5 Qxd5 8. Bxf4 Bg4 9. Be2 $6 (9. Bd3 $1 Be7 10. O-O {gains a plus.}) 9...
Bd6 10. Qd2 O-O 11. O-O Re8 {Black has developed adequately.} 12. Rae1 Nd7 13.
c3 (13. c4 Bxf4 14. Qxf4 Qe4 {exchange too.}) 13... Nf6 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. Bc4
Bxf3 16. Rxf3 Rxe1+ 17. Qxe1 Re8 18. Qg3 Qxg3 19. hxg3 Re1+ 20. Rf1 Rxf1+ 21.
Bxf1 Ne4 22. g4 g6 23. Bd3 Ng5 24. Kf2 Kg7 25. Ke3 Kf6 26. a4 Ke6 27. b4 Kd5
28. c4+ Kd6 29. Bc2 b6 30. c5+ bxc5 31. bxc5+ Kd7 32. Bb3 a5 33. Kf4 f6 34. Ke3
Ne6 35. Ke4 Ng5+ 36. Ke3 Ne6 37. Ke4 Ke7 38. Bc4 Ng5+ 39. Ke3 Nf7 40. Bxf7 Kxf7
41. d5 $2 cxd5 42. Kd4 Ke6 43. c6 Kd6 44. c7 Kxc7 45. Kxd5 Kb6 $2 (45... Kd7 $1
46. Kc5 h5 $1 {wins for Black.}) 46. Kd6 h5 47. gxh5 gxh5 48. Ke6 Kc5 49. Kxf6
{This opening can lead to equality quickly by fast exchanges.} 1/2-1/2

